text=(:nogroupheader:)%0a(:Summary::)%0a(:Published::)%0a(:Author:[[~GiverofMemory]]:)%0a(:License:[[https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Res_communis|Site License]]:)%0a(:Update::)%0a(:Maintainer:[[~GiverofMemory]]:)%0a(:Creator:[[]]:)%0a(:Categories:[[!Cryptics]]:)%0a(:Also:none:)%0a(:Archive:[[|Archive.is]], [[|Archive.org]]:)%0a(:Download:[[{$FullName}?action=print|URL]],[[https://www.web2pdfconvert.com/|PDF from URL]]:)%0a%0aDecent (but skewed to 1mb perspective) discussion of the blocksize debate [[https://bitcoinmagazine.com/guides/what-is-the-bitcoin-block-size-limit|#]]%0a%0aAnother skewed article reporting on elons (I believe 100%25 correct) views [[https://bitcoinmagazine.com/culture/elon-musk-wrong-bitcoin-block-size|#]] one argument made by the writer is that keeping the 1mb limit will lead to more nodes in the future.  I think it is threading a needle, small size is nice but not if the blockchain isn't usable by normal people due to too high fees and slow initial confirmation.%0a%0aAverage webpage size scaled from 1mb in 2011 to 3mb in 2017 [[https://www.speedcurve.com/blog/web-performance-page-bloat/|#]] from 2011+ according to httparchive.org [[https://getbutterfly.com/why-is-web-page-size-important/|#]] pre 2011 [[https://blog.radware.com/applicationdelivery/wpo/2013/11/web-page-growth-151-percent/|#]] [[https://www.yottaa.com/a-brief-history-of-web-page-size/|#]]%0a%0aWeb page size is doubling every 5 years [[https://getbutterfly.com/why-is-web-page-size-important/|#]] which may be a good target trajectory for blocksize to follow.
